Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure size limits in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Configure form options to enforce the 10MB limit
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(options =>
{
    options.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
});
```

**If using Kestrel, also set the request body limit:**

```csharp
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(options =>
{
    options.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

**The upload endpoint:**

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    // Validate content type
    string[] allowed = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are accepted.");

    // Validate size (defense-in-depth; FormOptions also enforces this)
    const long maxSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File exceeds the 10 MB limit.");

    // Ensure uploads directory exists
    var uploadsDir = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsDir);

    // Generate a safe, unique filename preserving the original extension
    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (ext is not ".jpg" and not ".jpeg" and not ".png")
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    var fileName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsDir, fileName);

    await using var stream = File.Create(filePath);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName, size = file.Length });
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // required for non-browser API clients
```

**Key points:**

- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** — since you already call `UseAntiforgery()`, multipart form posts will be rejected without a valid antiforgery token. `.DisableAntiforgery()` opts this endpoint out. If browser-only, remove it and send the token instead.
- **`Guid.NewGuid()`** prevents path traversal and filename collisions — never use the raw user-supplied filename.
- Content type *and* extension are both validated (content type can be spoofed, so the extension check adds defense-in-depth).
- `FormOptions.MultipartBodyLengthLimit` rejects oversized payloads at the framework level before your code runs.
